even if your `variable` is declared as `varchar(max)` what you get out of concatenation is a string of `8000` characters.

    declare @s varchar(max);
    
    set @s = replicate(&#39;a&#39;, 10000);
    select len(@s) as len_;
    --len_
    ---------
    --8000
    
    set @s = replicate(cast(&#39;a&#39; as varchar(max)), 10000);
    select len(@s) as len_;
    
    --len_
    --------
    --10000

