You dont need that while loop in your ````Method1()````. Rearrange your function to something like this:
````
private static boolean Method1() {
    //Do something   
    //if success happened, set it to false       
    return success;
}
````
I also recommend you to use ````while(!Method1());````. It makes the Code more understandable when you need to work at it later.

Alternatively change the whole architecture:
````
static boolean success = false;

public static void main(String[] args) {
    while(!success)
      Method1();
}

private static void Method1() {
    //Do something          
    //When Goal reached, set success = true
}
````

I think this is a cleaner way of solving your problem.
