Use [FocusNode Class][1], this will keep a track of when you have the focus on that particular `TextFormField`. 

**Note:** Make sure you assign different `FocusNode` object to different `TextFormField()` if you have multiple class.

Here is your solution: 

```
FocusNode _focusNode;

@override
void dispose() {
  super.dispose();
  _focusNode.dispose();
}

@override
void initState() {
  super.initState();
  _focusNode = new FocusNode();
  _focusNode.addListener(_onOnFocusNodeEvent);
}

_onOnFocusNodeEvent() {
  setState(() {
    // Re-renders
  });
}

TextFormField(
  focusNode: _focusNode
  decoration: InputDecoration(
     border: InputBorder.none,
     prefixIcon: Padding(
       padding: EdgeInsets.all(0.0),
       child: Icon(
         Icons.search,
         color: this.getPrefixIconColor(),
       ) // icon is 48px widget.
     )
   )
)

//This will change the color of the icon based upon the focus on the field
Color getPrefixIconColor(){
  return _focusNode.hasFocus ? Colors.black : Colors.grey
}
```

