The Windows version my software is 2-3 times slower than the Linux version. To debug that and to demonstrate the problem I have created three simple benchmark functions:

*  benchDouble() carries out some double precision computations
*  benchCgalSimple() computes the intersection of two lines without high-precision numbers
*  benchCgalGmpq() computes the glancing intersection of two lines such that GMPQ numbers are required

I have tuned the loops such that on my reference machine each function takes ~5 seconds:

