The next function, `getPaths`, is an adaptation of one from [another SO answer][so].  It lists all the paths in your object in the format used by `path` and `assocPath`, returning an array of values which are integers if the relevant nested object is an array and strings otherwise.  Unlike the function from which is was borrowed, it only returns paths to leaf values.

